      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "# Latest AI News Today\n\nHere's a roundup of the most notable AI stories making headlines today:\n\n## Major Legal Battle: Musk vs. OpenAI Trial\nThe high-profile legal showdown between Elon Musk and OpenAI is dominating headlines. "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The civil trial between the tech billionaires kicked off Monday and could help define the future of artificial intelligence. The trial is scheduled to run for four weeks, with a cast of prominent tech executives set to take the stand."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Jury selection wrapped Monday, and Musk testified Tuesday in the $134B suit to return OpenAI's assets to the nonprofit and oust Altman."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Musk was at times boastful and snarky, using the witness stand to attack Sam Altman and as a platform to score points against other tech rivals, claiming Altman betrayed the original principles of OpenAI to remain a nonprofit and that the company benefited from his money and connections."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## Big Tech Earnings & AI Investment Surge\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Alphabet Q1 beat estimates with $109.9B revenue; Google Cloud surged 63% to $20B as AI capex was raised to $190B."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Microsoft Q3 beat estimates; its AI business hit a $37B annual run rate, up 123% YoY."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Amazon Q1 beat estimates with $181.5B revenue; AWS posted 28% growth, the fastest in 15 quarters."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "OpenAI missed revenue targets, dragging Oracle and chip stocks down with it."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## AI Security Concerns\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "An AI company's own experts warned that \"Mythos\" could hack the systems beneath most modern computing, and banks and government agencies are racing to gauge the threat."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## Government & Defense AI\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Google has joined OpenAI in allowing the Pentagon to use its AI systems, while rival Anthropic remains embroiled in a court battle after seeking stronger safeguards."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The high-stakes conflict between the Defense Department and a $380 billion tech powerhouse goes to the heart of just how far AI can go in warfare."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## Regulation & Policy\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Florida Governor DeSantis is emerging as a voice of AI skepticism in the Republican Party, but state lawmakers declined to take up his push for legislation."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "A bill that had passed both chambers of the state Legislature would have imposed the country's first statewide moratorium on new data center construction."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Seven families of Tumbler Ridge shooting victims have sued OpenAI and Sam Altman in federal court."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## AI Industry & Applications\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Many companies are increasingly looking to AI agents as a way to boost employee productivity and automate rote chores."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Amazon Connect Talent – now available in preview – uses AI \"teammates\" to conduct 24/7 interviews and score candidates, easing the hiring process."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Rogo, started by young bankers around a kitchen table in 2021, just won a multibillion-dollar valuation, and Roblox is set to challenge Unity and Unreal engines with new AI software."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Actor Matthew McConaughey filed trademarks to protect his likeness against unauthorized AI replications."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## Research Highlights from MIT\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "A new dataset of 30,000-plus competition math problems from 47 countries gives AI researchers a harder test — and students worldwide a better training ground."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "A new training method improves the reliability of AI confidence estimates without sacrificing performance, addressing a root cause of hallucination in reasoning models."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "A new debiasing technique called WRING avoids creating or amplifying biases that can occur with existing debiasing approaches."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## Infrastructure Concerns\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Nuclear AI startup Fermi promised land and ample power but couldn't sign a single client. Now the ex-CEO is waging a battle for Fermi's future and its vision of atomic-powered data centers in the Texas panhandle."
